            "type": "text",
            "title": "While... 🔁",
            "content": "A `while` loop is simpler. It keeps running **while** a condition is true.\n\nYou use it when you don't know exactly how many times you need to loop."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l3_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "When does a while loop stop?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "When the condition becomes false",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "After 10 times always",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "It checks the condition before every iteration."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "While Example ⏳",
            "content": "Print numbers until `count` is 3.",
            "codeSnippet": "let count = 0;\n\nwhile (count < 3) {\n  console.log(count);\n  count++;\n}",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_4",
            "type": "tip",
            "title": "Infinite Loop! ♾️",
            "content": "## Careful!\n\nIf the condition never becomes false, your loop will run forever and crash your browser!\n\nAlways make sure something changes (like `count++`)!"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_5",
